This paper deals with graph embeddings and graph coloring, which are central topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the complexity of decision problems related to edge partitions, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper presents results on maximum vertex degree, which is a fundamental concept in graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses applications of the results to graph drawing, which is a subfield of computer graphics and visualization (cs.GT).
